My legs, (especially my right one) were hurting since yesterday afternoon, thanks to my bad cartwheel landing. I pulled a string or probably stretched my muscles in the wrong way. But I wrapped my right leg with a bandage overnight, and kept it on the whole day in school. I must say, this helped a lot. I did not cramp-up or hurt with the soreness I expected. I even walked semi-straight&nbsp;<font size="1">(see I wore my 5-minute shoes--quite high from my ordinary shoes&nbsp;that it slowly "killed" me, thus my semi-straight walking)</font> today, and to think that I couldn't even walk straight after my bad landing yesterday.&nbsp;<br /><br />I can't believe I made it to 5 rounds around the jogging path. It's been <u><strong>years</strong></u> (think college) since I last ran [as a form of exercise]. I thought I'd only last 3 rounds,... <em>even less actually</em>. But for some reason, I had the energy to go on beyond 3. I'll try to sprint next time.&nbsp;I guess all the dancing, stair-climbing, brisk walking from one end of the faculty room to the other and from GS to HS (and vice versa) has paid off somehow.&nbsp;I am so tired and yet I feel so much more energized. Whoohoo. I love exercising!<br /><br /><div class="ljcut" text="Random story #1">So Ian <span class="ljuser"><img style="VERTICAL-ALIGN: bottom" height="17" alt="" width="17" src="/stc/fck/editor/plugins/livejournal/userinfo.gif" />ianysip</span>&nbsp;has decided to post Ateneo photos he took, <em>I'm guessing</em> recently. And I can't help but feel&nbsp;jealous.<br />I feel jealous of two things: The first one is how he lives so near Ateneo, and how he could easily drop by, visit and shoot. the second thing I'm jealous of is his "shooting" time. Why-oh-why do you have the free time to take photographs, while I don't? <font size="1">(Don't answer, as we both know the answer.)</font> Hehe.</div><br /><div class="ljcut" text="Hey shawty, it's yer birthday">It's Ms. Maud's birthday today. <em>Happy Birthday Miss Mauds!</em> Also Ms. Gcel's, Ms. Irene's and Ms. Beth's. <em>Happy birthday&nbsp;Ms. Gcel, Ms. Irene and Ms. Beth!</em>&nbsp;I would have wanted to post&nbsp; digital birthday cards, but I didn't have the luxury to fiddle with Photoshop and chase these one-in-a-million birthday&nbsp;celebs for a photograph.&nbsp;So, um... belated digital birthday cards perhaps? <br /><br />Would I ever forget another birthday girl? HAPPY BIRTHDAY to the JINGerbells! <span class="ljuser"><img style="VERTICAL-ALIGN: bottom" height="17" alt="" width="17" src="/stc/fck/editor/plugins/livejournal/userinfo.gif" />jhoanna</span> *mwah* My lovable vegetarian, bohemian&nbsp;friend. I miss you. I will write you a message along with the belated digital birthday card I will make. Ok? :)</div><br />Sadly, I've no photos to share tonight. Anyway. Until I do... here's one more random moment....<br /><br /><font size="1"><strong><u>Ang&nbsp;usapang Cherry Rodeo at Mitzi:<br /></u></strong>Cherry: Gusto mo bang kunin ang klase ko sa I-1 o I-2 sa susunod na linggo?<br />Mitzi: Hah? *blinks* Kailan uli ito? *looks at the calendar* Sa 21?<br />Cherry: Hindi, sa susunod na linggo... sa 28.<br />Mitzi: Oo nga, sa 21 nga.<br />Cherry: Hindi, sa 28 pa nga.&nbsp;<br />Mitzi: Teka, anong araw na ba tayo ngayon?<br />Cherry: 19 na po. Umagang-umaga nawawala ka na naman sa sarili!<br /></font><br /><em>hehehe.</em><br />I'm forgetful and date-disoriented. <strong>O_o<br /></strong><br />*+*+*+*+*+*+*+*+*<br />p.s. <strong>RYAN AGONCILLO is&nbsp;<u>one</u> <u>fine</u> <u>man</u></strong>. *sigh*&nbsp;<br /><em>Elaineybee, Ryan's your cousin right?</em>
